    <p>	As a front-end developer there are a lot of different technologies to keep up with. Whether I’m working with AngularJS or trying to set up Grunt tasks, I find myself having to look up a lot of things. To make that easier on myself, I decided to write Google Chrome extensions to simplify the process. It turns out that’s pretty darn easy! In this article, I’ll show you how to create a simple one that hooks into Chrome's Omnibar to search the Drupal API with a simple keyword.</p>
